# BeepBeep AI — admin design system rules

When editing `admin/**` partials or enqueue-related PHP:

## Use shared primitives

- **Buttons:** `bbai-btn` + `bbai-btn-primary` / `bbai-btn-secondary` / `bbai-btn-sm` (see `assets/css/system/bbai-admin-controls.css`). Do not add page-only button shadows, radii, or font-weight overrides unless the change is added to the shared control layer.
- **Form fields:** `bbai-input`, `bbai-select`, `bbai-textarea` with shared labels (`bbai-section-label`).
- **Cards:** `bbai-card` and modifiers (`bbai-card--soft`, `bbai-card--pad-md`) from `bbai-admin-surfaces.css`.
- **Section headings:** `bbai-section-header`, `bbai-ui-section-header`, `bbai-section-label`, `bbai-section-title`, `bbai-section-description`.
- **Workflow colour:** badges, filters, row rails, and “health” callouts must use **`--bbai-status-*`** / `bbai-badge--*` / semantic status CSS — not one-off hex for missing vs review vs optimized.
- **Tables:** prefer `bbai-table` and workspace row patterns from `bbai-admin-table-workspace.css` on dashboard-scoped pages.

## Avoid drift

- **No new inline `<style>` blocks** for layout, colour, or typography. Add or extend `assets/css/system/*.css` (or an existing feature sheet) and enqueue via `admin/traits/trait-core-assets.php`.
- **No parallel token families** like new `--bbai-page-foo-*` in PHP; extend `bbai-admin-foundation-tokens.css` or unified tokens.
- **Body scope:** plugin screens use `body.bbai-dashboard`; new global selectors should be scoped the same way.

## References

- `docs/design-system/README.md` — index and load order  
- `docs/design-system/REFERENCE.md` — components, anti-patterns, backlog  

## PHP enqueue order

Do not change stylesheet dependency order in `trait-core-assets.php` without checking: foundation → controls → surfaces → semantic status → table workspace → page adoption / library polish.
